c_i \in \{0,1\}
i
c_i = 1
c_1,...,c_4
X(c) = c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4
n-X(c) = 4-X(c) = 4-(c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4)
M(c) = \max(X(c), 4-X(c)) = \max(c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4, 4-(c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4))
c
E M = \frac{1}{16} \sum_{c \in \{0,1\}^4} \max(c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4, 4-(c_1+c_2+c_3+c_4))
E M = \frac{1}{16} (4 \cdot (1+1) + 3 \cdot (4+4) + 2 \cdot (6)) = \frac{11}{4}
